	     Johannesburg - President Jacob Zuma is appealing the North Gauteng High Court judgment on state capture. Last Wednesday, December 13, a full bench of the North Gauteng High Court unanimously found that Zuma's review application of former public Protector Thuli Madonsela's recommendations on alleged state capture was ill advised and reckless. READ: #StateCapture judgment: 13 blows dealt to Zuma, quote by quote Zuma wanted the court to set aside the remedial actions in Madonsela's State of Capture report which also called for Chief Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng to choose the judge to oversee the commission of inquiry into state capture. The facts speak for the president's clearly unreasonable stance, said Mlambo. The court also found that Zuma must also be held personally liable for the legal cost. More to follow. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  